<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871020-0080 </DOCNO><HL> Who's News:American Vision TapsVan Ekris and BarlerinFor Top 2 Positions</HL><DD> 10/20/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> AMVC WNEWS KAY </IN><DATELINE> NEW YORK  </DATELINE><TEXT>   American Vision Centers Inc. named Anthonie C. van Ekris chairman and Michael C. Barlerin president and chief operating officer.    They succeed Robert S. Cohen, 43 years old, former chairman and president, who remains a director. His brothers, Alan R. Cohen and Edward M. Cohen, resigned as directors, as did Robert Gertler.    Mr. van Ekris, 53, is chairman of Kay Corp., a New York-based commodity trader and broker that last week acquired a 52% stake in the retail eye-care chain. Mr. Barlerin, 46, was formerly senior vice president and director of marketing for Zale Corp., a Dallas-based jewelry retailer.    In addition to Mr. van Ekris, Thomas E. Hitselberger and John C. Belknap were named to American Vision Centers' board, succeeding Messrs. Cohen and Gertler. Mr. Hitselberger is chief financial officer of Kay Corp. and Mr. Belknap is chief financial officer of Seligman andamp; Latz Inc., a closely held New York-based jewelry concern. </TEXT></DOC>